Governing terms of use
----------------------

  Digital Agency "Illustration & Icon Materials Terms of Use"
  https://www.digital.go.jp/policies/servicedesign/designsystem/Illustration_Icons/terms_of_use

Key points (informal summary; the linked terms are authoritative):

  - Commercial use is permitted.
  - Reproduction, public transmission, translation, and adaptation are
    permitted.
  - When materials are used as-is, credit attribution is not required.
  - When materials are edited or adapted and then redistributed, the
    source must be cited and the fact that they were modified must be
    indicated.
  - Materials must not be presented in a manner that suggests they were
    created by the national government of Japan.

Modifications applied to the icon assets in this package
--------------------------------------------------------

The original SVG files were transformed by `scripts/build-icons.ts` before
being embedded into the bundle:

  - `fill="#1A1A1C"` was replaced with `fill="currentColor"` so that the
    icon color follows the host element's CSS `color` property.
  - The `width` and `height` attributes on the root `<svg>` element were
    removed so the icon size is controlled via CSS.
  - The XML prolog, comments, and inter-tag whitespace were stripped, and
    each SVG was inlined as a JavaScript string for runtime injection
    into the Shadow DOM of the `<dga-icon>` Web Component.

No changes were made to the icon path data (`<path d="...">`).

